e' ) I am yet to hear of any gm interaction of note, much less of a roleplaying nature. Quite frankly I expected a little more than a fishing derby ( as fun as that was ). Maybe it is time the player community picked up the ball on this..... NO scavenger hunts =P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cyndar>Cyndar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/22/01 10:40:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=945.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We need a server event!!</span><hr size=1> Yea, i always read Everlore about GM events since i began playing EQ sometime around June and i cant really remember any GM events on this server maybe a couple that i might recall reading about but I always see events on other servers on Everlore.<br><br>i think your right, the players should get something going..we could even send the event to Everlore and they would post it on the site so a larger amount of people will read about the event and when what and where etc.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unakath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nakath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/23/01 1:39:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=945.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We need a server event!!</span><hr size=1> I have a /played under 10 days and have seen 3 GM events already... I think you're missing the importance of size of group to GM ratio when you are looking for events.<br><br>The GMs on FV, in what I have observed, look for small groups to pop events on, instead of the PC Loot Bum-Rush that happens on traditional servers.<br><br>Moreover, the smaller events DO seem connected (like they have a common plot or thread) and are not 'stock' events...<br><br>The GMs at Verant are (very obviously) not professional Paper and Pencil GMs (and, yes, there are professional paler and pencil GMs out there, who do make money at it). Regardless, they are getting better at running events, plotting, and figuring out how to work with large groups and the entire dynamic of large group events.<br><br>Since the best way to get good at plotting is to use smaller gorups of players, i APPLAUD them for not having meat-market 50-100 person 'scavenger hunt' events.<br><br>These 'scavenger hunt' and 'scripted' events (like that piece of shit Lanys T'Vyl thing they did) are frequently CRAP, have no real plot or interaction with the players. It is a 'run on rails' event... the players have no input or say in the outcome.<br><br>At least the GMs here seem to trust us, the players, and I like that. <p>Nakath<BR>The Esoteric Order</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uartillis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Artillis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/23/01 7:11:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=945.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We need a server event!!</span><hr size=1> There have been a numbe of GM events and will continue to be a number of SMALL GM events.  You just won't hear of them and may never hear of many of them unless in a guild.  The other night some of my guild members were in lower guk dead side and were the only ones there, a misterious new creature called a crazy froglock appeared, it ended up being a very small GM event hardly even worth being mentioned, but was still fun for those involved.<br><br>Also a similar thing happened in south Karana.  GM events happen, if you are not there you will not see them and may never hear of them, end of story.<br><br>On a side note it has been some time sence I have personaly witnessed a GM event, I havn't been in the right place at the right time.  I just hear about some of them from guild members becase they WERE in the right place at the right time.   <br><br>My advice, play the game, role play, have fun, and if an event happens have fun with it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uelsbetsquishytoes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>elsbet squishytoes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Grey</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/23/01 7:46:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=945.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We need a server event!!</span><hr size=1> What would be neat here is if players could submit small scale quests that have no real effect on Norrath.  I am roleplaying a scenario in which Alice Sweetoven, a merchant in the cleric guild in Rivervale, gets married to Deputy Budo, to escape the drudgery of selling spells all day.  This would remove Alice from RV, but she could be replaced by another cashier, yes?<br><br>Having *actual* changes to the world we are supposed to be roleplaying on would be fun.  Probably a poor waste of programmers' time, on one of the least populated servers, but this would be a lot of fun if it was feasible.<br><br>I am yet to see a GM event here, though I have heard of a few, but the two guides I have run into here played their roles very well, /salute Narzis in particular. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugrimwyrd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimwyrd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/23/01 8:07:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=945.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We need a server event!!</span><hr size=1> I (and maybe 38-40 others) took part in a GM-sponsored fishing contest Friday in East Freeport. It was pretty fun even though my ISP crapped out and I went LD with 6 minutes of fishing to go. They handed out poles and bait, and awarded prizes. <p>Grimwyrd Storm<BR>(Lux Aeternam)<BR>28th Human Druid of Karana<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufalconeroftunare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falconer of Tunare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/23/01 8:52:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=945.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We need a server event!!</span><hr size=1> /ooc<br><br>I think this thread has been hijacked. GM events or no, it would be great if we could get a decent player run event going.<br>I've seen many planned, but quite often they 