>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We need a server event!!</span><hr size=1>       I like the small GM events, there was one last week in Highhold. A demented orc was handing out pickles and bleeding brains and showing his lack of IQ but had a great sense of humor. He left when the higher characters finally showed up to try to kill him. That is why I like the smaller events. You do not have someone interrupting the story line every 10 seconds when they try to kill the GM controlled npc.<br><br>Lexxi<br>20th Prayer<br>Cleric of Brell<br>Ak'Anon<br>Officer - Ledenyetz Troupe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umirkhan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mirkhan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/27/01 12:27:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=945.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We need a server event!!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I like the small GM events, there was one last week in Highhold. A demented orc was handing out pickles and bleeding brains and showing his lack of IQ but had a great sense of humor. He left when the higher characters finally showed up to try to kill him. That is why I like the smaller events. You do not have someone interrupting the story line every 10 seconds when they try to kill the GM controlled npc.<br></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>I heard the new changes make it possible for an NPC to be &quot;non-targettable&quot;. This is probably what can be done to Event NPCs if the GMs dont want people to interrupt the event or their speeches. <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=htt